def emissions (platform):
    print(platform)
    q1 = new_df.loc[new_df['platform'] == platform, 'total_sales'].quantile(0.25) #    
    q3 = new_df.loc[new_df['platform'] == platform, 'total_sales'].quantile(0.75) #    
    iqr = q3 - q1 #  
    print(f'    : {q1 - 1.5 * iqr, q3 + 1.5 * iqr}') 
    print('   :', new_df.loc[new_df['platform'] == platform]['total_sales'].min()) #   =   
    print(' :', new_df.query('platform == @ platform and total_sales > @ q3 + 1.5 * @ iqr')['total_sales'].count())
    return new_df.query('platform == @ platform and total_sales > @ q3 + 1.5 * @ iqr').sample()
display(emissions("3DS"))
display(emissions("PC"))
display(emissions("PS4"))
display(emissions("WiiU"))
display(emissions("XOne"))

#       
def genres (genre):
    print(genre)
    q1 = new_df.loc[new_df['genre'] == genre, 'total_sales'].quantile(0.25) #    
    q3 = new_df.loc[new_df['genre'] == genre, 'total_sales'].quantile(0.75) #    
    iqr = q3 - q1 #  
    print(f'    : {q1 - 1.5 * iqr, q3 + 1.5 * iqr}') 
    print(' :', new_df.query('genre == @ genre and total_sales > @ q3 + 1.5 * @ iqr')['total_sales'].count())
    return new_df.query('genre == @ genre and total_sales > @ q3 + 1.5 * @ iqr').sample()
